<HEADLINE>
<P>
L. RON HUBBARD'S CHURCH OF SCIENTOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times and staff writers Joel Sappell and Robert Welkos have done a 
commendable public service with the series on Hubbard and the Church of 
Scientology. 
</P>
<P>
While not as blatantly destructive as the Rev. Jim Jones' Peoples Temple, the 
Church of Scientology is nevertheless a threat to American society. 
</P>
<P>
Scientology has tried to justify and protect itself by citing the 
constitutional guarantee of freedom of religion. Freedom of religion does not 
include the freedom to exploit, deceive or harass others. 
</P>
<P>
JERRY FALLENBERG 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
