<HEADLINE>
<P>
L. RON HUBBARD'S CHURCH OF SCIENTOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I would like to thank The Times for the free publicity for the Church of 
Scientology. This advertisement must have cost several hundred thousand 
dollars. 
</P>
<P>
I am a mechanical engineer working in a Fortune 100 company, and have been a 
Scientologist only a short while (just over two years). However, I have 
improved so much in just these few months that I wish I had at least heard of 
Scientology earlier in my life. 
</P>
<P>
Some of my gains have been in the area of communication skills which is the 
backbone of everything that we do, everyday. I have also become very innovative 
and have filed several patents since that time. This is an ability that I did 
not think I had. My affinity for others has gone up tremendously. I can also 
see other people's point of view which makes me a very fair person indeed. I 
have become such a role model at work that people with four times as much 
experience as me come to me for advice, on not only work-related matters but 
also personal issues. I can think very clearly without any sidetracks. I feel 
great, and have never been happier in my life. I owe it all to Hubbard, his 
discovery of Dianetics and Scientology, and the correct application of his 
findings. 
</P>
<P>
Your articles will have a positive impact by generating interest and curiosity 
among readers. Eventually they will want to know more and will stop by a 
Scientology organization and sign up for services. 
</P>
<P>
JOSEPH ESKANDARI 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
