<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old Del Mar boy died of massive internal injuries after a car in 
which he was riding slammed into a tree. The driver, another 16-year-old boy 
from Del Mar, was arrested at the hospital on suspicion of felony drunk driving 
and manslaughter, said a spokesman for the California Highway Patrol in 
Oceanside. 
</P>
<P>
The driver's name was not released because he is a minor. He was also 
hospitalized. 
</P>
<P>
Jeffrey James Foote, who was one of three passengers, died at 6:15 a.m. Monday 
at Scripps Memorial Hospital in La Jolla, about six hours after the accident, 
said Jerry Bohrer of the CHP. 
</P>
<P>
Bohrer said the four were traveling west on Via de la Valle, west of La Gracia 
at about 75 m.p.h. when the driver went off the road and broadsided a tree. 
</P>
<P>
"It was with such force that the passenger door was pushed into the car 2 1/2 
feet," Bohrersaid. He said that Foote, sitting in the front passenger seat, 
took the brunt of the impact and was pinned inside the car. 
</P>
<P>
The other passengers, 16-year-old Ruben Gutierrez and 16-year-old Kevin Kirby, 
both of Solana Beach, were taken to Scripps Memorial Hospital in Encinitas. 
Kirby was treated and released Monday, and Gutierrez was discharged from the 
hospital Tuesday, a hospital spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
