<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATUE IN POPE'S CHURCH DEFACED; AMERICAN HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An American was arrested Tuesday after reportedly throwing red paint on a 
17th-Century statue of St. Paul in the basilica of St. John Lateran, the Pope's 
church as bishop of Rome, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said a man dressed as a clergyman threw a bottle filled with red 
paint at the marble statue near the entrance of the church. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas Siener, 50, was arrested shortly after the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
