<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE TEACHERS MUST SPEAK ENGLISH, LAW SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HARRISBURG, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. Robert P. Casey has signed a bill intended to help college students better 
understand their instructors. The new law, signed Monday, requires colleges and 
universities to certify to the state that their instructors are fluent in 
English. 
</P>
<P>
State Sen. Vincent Fumo, who sponsored the measure, has said that students have 
been complaining that they cannot understand some of their instructors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
