<HEADLINE>
<P>
11 KILLED BY SIKH MILITANTS IN INDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHANDIGARH, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sikh militants in northern Punjab state killed at least 11 people, including a 
former state finance minister who was gunned down in downtown Chandigarh, 
police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Balwant Singh, the former Punjab state finance minister, was 
returning home in his car with two bodyguards and his driver after visiting a 
friend when the attack occurred. All four were killed by three gunmen. 
</P>
<P>
At least seven other people were killed by militants in a spate of attacks 
around the strife-torn state Monday night and early Tuesday, police said. 
</P>
