<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Delta Cuts L.A.-to-San Francisco Fares: Delta Air Lines, following the lead of 
California's other major carriers, slashed fares between San Francisco and Los 
Angeles to as low as $58 round trip. 
</P>
<P>
The $58 fare applies only to tickets purchased 21 days in advance for travel on 
any day except Friday and Sunday. Seven-day advance tickets can be purchased 
for $78 on off-peak days and $84 on Fridays and Sundays. One-day advance fares 
of $98 round trip are available seven days a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
