<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: LILLIE IS NEW COO AT AMERICAN PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Lucky Stores chief executive John M. Lillie has been named to the new 
position of president and chief operating officer of American President Cos., 
an Oakland-based ocean and rail transportation company. 
</P>
<P>
Lillie, 53, was chairman and chief executive of California supermarket giant 
Lucky Stores Inc. when it was bought by American Stores Co. of Salt Lake City 
in 1988. He left the company in 1989 after the $2.5-billion merger was 
completed and joined the venture capital firm Sequoia Associates in Menlo Park, 
Calif., as a general partner. 
</P>
<P>
At American President, he will oversee both the company's Pacific Basin 
shipping line, American President Lines and its domestic freight business, 
American President Domestic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
