<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES; 
</P>
<P>
IRVINE HIGH SCHOOL NAMES NEW ATHLETIC DIRECTORS, COACHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Curtis has been named athletic director at Irvine High School, replacing 
Barry Schulenburg, who resigned. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, Curtis was an assistant football and basketball coach, and golf 
coach at Irvine. Previously, he had been football coach at University High. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Limp has been named assistant athletic director at Irvine. She had been 
the girls' athletic director but wanted to devote more time to coaching 
softball. 
</P>
<P>
Also at Irvine: Darrell Prescott has been named boys' soccer coach, and Mark 
Mednick has been named boys' volleyball coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
