<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MAN, 20, FOUND SHOT TO DEATH IN ANAHEIM; 3 INTRUDERS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old man was shot to death in an Anaheim apartment by three intruders, 
authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
Officers found the man, whose identity was not confirmed, lying on the living 
room floor of the apartment with a single gunshot wound to his chest, said 
Anaheim Police Officer John Oldroyd. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics pronounced the man dead at the scene, Oldroyd said. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred about 9:20 p.m. Tuesday in an apartment on East Banyan 
Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The man was with two friends when three intruders entered an open front door, 
brandishing a knife, handgun and rifle, Oldroyd said. The invaders ordered the 
victim's two friends to go to a back room and remain there. 
</P>
<P>
A short time later, the friends told police, they heard a single gunshot, 
Oldroyd said. They waited a few minutes, then went into the living room and 
found the victim lying on the floor. The three intruders had fled. 
</P>
<P>
It was not apparent whether anything had been taken from the apartment, Oldroyd 
said. Investigators were unsure whether the shooting was drug- or gang-related, 
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
