<P>
EASTER BUSINESS HELPS SAFEWAY TRIPLE PROFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OAKLAND 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Safeway Inc. reported a tripling of second-quarter profits today, reflecting 
improved gross margins and sales from the Easter shopping season. 
</P>
<P>
The supermarket chain said net income jumped 206.5% to $23.6 million, or 25 
cents a share, from $7.7 million, or 10 cents a share, in the comparable 
quarter of 1989. 
</P>
