<P>
GUBICZA ON ROYALS DISABLED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KANSAS CITY, Mo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Kansas City Royals placed starting pitcher Mark Gubicza on the 21-day 
disabled list today, retroactive to June 30. 
</P>
<P>
The right-hander, who is 4-7 with a 4.50 earned-run average, is suffering from 
inflammation in his right shoulder. He is expected to resume throwing in two 
weeks. 
</P>
<P>
To replace Gubicza, the Royals purchased the contract of right-hander Jay 
Baller from the Omaha Royals, the club's Triple-A affiliate. 
</P>
<P>
Baller is 2-4 with a 3.47 ERA and 12 saves in 31 relief appearances. 
</P>
